Visit nsw.gov.au for more information.

properties.adviceB: Exercise caution; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:

The restrictions will remain in place until temporary repair work can be carried out.

Motorists crossing the bridge will also experience delays, with traffic control and a reduced speed limit of 40km/h in place
properties.diversions:
Vehicles of more than 22 tonnes use an alternative route via Giinagay Way
and the Pacific Hwy, which will add about 25 minutes travelling time.

properties.headline: COVID-19 Border Pass Requirements for Freight - TWEED HEADS M1 Pacific Motorway approaching Queensland border
properties.otherAdvice:
The Queensland state government has imposed restrictions at the NSW-QLD border as a result of the coronavirus pandemic.

Heavy vehicles intending to travel from New South Wales to Queensland must use the Gold Coast Highway and have a valid Freight and Logistics Pass (F Pass).

Border control measures can change quickly. Heavy vehicle operators are advised to visit the QLD Government website for up to date information on those eligible to travel and border pass requirements.

Heavy vehicle operators can also visit the National Heavy Vehicle Regulator - COVID-19 Support Map for assistance in finding service centres and roadhouses.
properties.displayName: COVID-19 Border Pass Requirements for Freight

properties.headline: SPECIAL EVENT CLEARWAYS - Bus operations - SURRY HILLS Chalmers Street between Cleveland Street AND Devonshire Street
properties.otherAdvice:
Special event clearways will be in effect on the western side of Chalmers St between Cleveland St and Devonshire St from 2am Saturday 7 August until 2am Monday 9 August to facilitate rail replacement bus operations for Light rail trackwork. 

Clearways are strict no-parking zones and apply even to local residents or RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs before parking as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

properties.headline: CRASH Car, Motorcycle - DEE WHY Pittwater Road approaching Fisher Road
CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - NORTH NOWRA Illaroo Road at Princes Highway
properties.otherAdvice:
Work to prepare to move traffic onto the lowered section of Illaroo Rd in the coming weeks will take place on Friday night to Saturday morning.
- Road users wishing to turn right out of Illaroo Rd onto the Princes Highway will be detoured northbound on the Princes Hwy and will use the Beinda St roundabout to travel south.  
- The left turn out of Illaroo Rd will be maintained at all times to allow for this detour.  
- Road users travelling south and wishing to turn right into Illaroo Rd will be detoured via the Princes Hwy, Moss St and the North St roundabout.  
- The northbound left turn lane into Illaroo Rd will be maintained during this work.
